# Testing (test-as-you-build)

Read [docs/TESTING.md](../../docs/TESTING.md) for full strategy.

## Non-negotiable (same PR as feature)

| Layer | When |
|-------|------|
| **Unit** | Utils, validators, isolated hook logic |
| **Integration** | Services, hooks, hook+UI flows (mocked Supabase/API) |
| **E2E (Maestro)** | New user-facing flows (≥1 happy path) |
| **Deno** | Edge Function auth, validation, error shapes |
| **Regression** | Every bug fix |

## Commands

```bash
npm test                      # unit + integration
npm run test:edge             # Deno Edge Functions
maestro test .maestro/flows/  # e2e
```

## Integration tests

Use `.integration.test.ts(x)` — test service + hook + component wiring with mocked I/O.

- Mock `@/lib/supabase` at boundary; use real service/hook code
- Wrap hooks in `QueryClientProvider` with `retry: false`
- Cover success **and** failure paths (401, validation, max tags)

## E2E

Add stable `testID` to interactive elements:

```tsx
<Pressable testID="new-memory-save" ... />
```

## Do not

- Merge major features with zero unit/integration tests on business logic
- Skip integration tests ("e2e is enough") — e2e is slow and flaky for edge cases
- Call real OpenAI/prod Supabase from unit/integration/CI
- Defer tests to a follow-up PR
